President Obama announced his intent to appoint several individuals to key Administration posts. Patricia Welbourn Lorsch, a former journalist, teacher, and political activist, will be appointed as a Member of the Advisory Committee on the Arts for the John F. Kennedy Center for the Performing Arts. Rusty Rueff, Chairman Emeritus of the GRAMMY Foundation, will also be appointed as a Member of the Advisory Committee on the Arts for the John F. Kennedy Center for the Performing Arts. Orlan Boston, a Principal at Ernst & Young LLP, will be appointed as a Member of the Board of Governors of the United Service Organizations, Incorporated. John D. Goldman, former President of the San Francisco Symphony, will be appointed as a General Trustee on the Board of Trustees of the John F. Kennedy Center for the Performing Arts. Amalia Perea Mahoney, former Director of Galeria Amalia Mahoney, will also be appointed as a General Trustee on the Board of Trustees of the John F. Kennedy Center for the Performing Arts. Alyssa Mastromonaco, a contributing editor to Marie Claire and former Assistant to the President and Deputy Chief of Staff, will be appointed as a General Trustee on the Board of Trustees of the John F. Kennedy Center for the Performing Arts. Reginald Van Lee, an Executive Vice President at Booz Allen Hamilton, will also be appointed as a General Trustee on the Board of Trustees of the John F. Kennedy Center for the Performing Arts. Danielle Gray, a litigation partner at Oâ€™Melveny & Myers LLP and former Assistant to the President and Cabinet Secretary, will be appointed as a Member of the Council of the Administrative Conference of the United States. Barry Thom, the Deputy Regional Administrator for the Fisheries Service of NOAA, will be appointed as the United States Commissioner for the Inter-American Tropical Tuna Commission. Allan Holt, a Managing Director at The Carlyle Group, will be appointed as a Member of the United States Holocaust Memorial Council.